docs.abstract: Cuyahoga County, Ohio, has used a waiver for years to avoid certain work requirements for many of its food-stamp recipients. Under new rules, that is about to end.
docs.snippet: Cuyahoga County, Ohio, has used a waiver for years to avoid certain work requirements for many of its food-stamp recipients. Under new rules, that is about to end.
docs.lead_paragraph: CLEVELAND — Next month, Cuyahoga County, Ohio’s second largest, will begin sending letters and fliers, making phone calls and hosting information fairs to alert struggling citizens of a change about to befall them: Come April, able-bodied adults without children may lose their food stamps if they do not find work fast.

headline.main: Cities Prepare for the Worst as Trump’s Food Stamp Cuts Near
headline.print_headline: Preparing for the Worst in Ohio as Cuts to Federal Food Benefits Loom

docs.abstract: In an extraordinary statement, Secretary of State Mike Pompeo criticized a veteran NPR reporter, Mary Louise Kelly, and said the news media was “unhinged.”
docs.snippet: In an extraordinary statement, Secretary of State Mike Pompeo criticized a veteran NPR reporter, Mary Louise Kelly, and said the news media was “unhinged.”
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Secretary of State Mike Pompeo escalated his clash with a respected NPR journalist on Saturday, lashing out at her and what he called the “unhinged” news media in an extraordinary statement. A day earlier, he abruptly ended an interview with her and delivered what the news outlet described as a profanity-laced rant.

headline.main: Pompeo Denounces News Media, Undermining U.S. Message on Press Freedom
headline.print_headline: Pompeo Ignites Outrage With Statement Reviling ‘Unhinged’ News Media
